  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Les Mélèzes is run by the Dode family who have been welcoming guests since 1968, they are renowned for their hospitality and will be sure to make you feel welcome. The hotel has great facilities such as a lovely wellness area to come back to after a day on the slopes, making this an ideal choice for a ski holiday.</p>
<h2>Great location</h2>
<p>The Hotel Les Mélèzes is ideally located in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/94b0461bf3c0472a89c38df58692ce28" href="/{localLink:umb://document/94b0461bf3c0472a89c38df58692ce28}" title="Les 2 Alpes">Les 2 Alpes</a> at the bottom of the piste, perfect for keen skiiers and boarders who want to get onto the fabulous <a data-udi="umb://document/94b0461bf3c0472a89c38df58692ce28" href="/{localLink:umb://document/94b0461bf3c0472a89c38df58692ce28}" title="Les 2 Alpes">Les Deux Alpes</a> slopes first thing. Returning to the hotel is equally as easy, plus there is a heated boot room so you can easily store all your equipment at the end of the day. As the hotel has a central location, the resort facilities, shops, bars and restaurants are only short walk away. </p>
<h2>Relax and unwind</h2>
<p>After a day of exploring the slopes, head back to the hotel and make the most of the hotels own wellness area. Soak away your achy ski legs in the jacuzzi, or relax in the sauna and enjoy a massage shower after. If relaxing isn't for you, there is also a fitness area with a range of machines to keep you in shape. To fully unwind, massages and treatments are available to book locally. </p>
<h2>Charm and character</h2>
<p>This chalet-style hotel combines comfort and cosiness, with the careful use of wood and warm colours inspired by the surroundings, creating a designer style atmosphere and cosy ambiance. <span>Each room is uniquely decorated in a contemporary Alpine style, and are well equipped for everything you need for a relaxing stay in the Alps.</span></p>]]></description>
