  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Rooms</strong> sleep two people and are around 14m². These rooms are simple and have traditional décor with north facing views of the village. These rooms are also available for single occupancy, please give our Reservations team a call to book.</p>
<p><strong>Traditional Rooms</strong> sleep two or three people and are around 19m². These modern style alpine rooms have two or three single beds, and south facing views overlooking the slopes.</p>
<p><strong>Family Comfort Rooms</strong> sleep two to four people and are around 26m². These cosy traditional style rooms have a double or twin beds, plus additional bunk beds. These rooms have south facing views, minimum of four people during Christmas, New Year and February French school holiday periods. </p>
<p><strong>Superior Cosy Double Rooms</strong> sleep two people and are around 17m². These rooms have been renovated in a traditional Alpine style, each room has a balcony with south facing views overlooking the Muzelle glacier.</p>
<p><strong>Junior suites</strong> sleep two people and are around 33-46m². These rooms vary in appearance, some of these bedrooms have a traditional style while others have a more traditional style, these rooms have a seating area and varying views of either the village or slopes. These rooms are on a request basis only, please call our Reservations team to book.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Room facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Views of the surrounding resort and/or mountains</li>
<li>En-suite bathroom with a shower or bathtub.</li>
<li>Satellite TV</li>
<li>Telephone</li>
<li>Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Baby cots are available on request</li>
<li>All rooms can take a cot</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
